Process called "create_color" that takes red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer returns Color:
    Let hsl_color be rgb_to_hsl with red as red and green as green and blue as blue
    Let oklch_color be rgb_to_oklch with red as red and green as green and blue as blue
    Let hex_string be rgb_to_hex with red as red and green as green and blue as blue
    
    Return Color with:
        red as red
        green as green
        blue as blue
        alpha as 1.0
        hsl as hsl_color
        oklch as oklch_color
        hex as hex_string

Note: Color Conversion Functions

Process called "rgb_to_hsl" that takes red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer returns HSLColor:
    Note: Convert RGB to HSL color space
    Let r be red as Float divided by 255.0
    Let g be green as Float divided by 255.0
    Let b be blue as Float divided by 255.0
    
    Let max_val be Math.maximum of (Math.maximum of r and g) and b
    Let min_val be Math.minimum of (Math.minimum of r and g) and b
    Let delta be max_val minus min_val
    
    Note: Calculate lightness
    Let lightness be (max_val plus min_val) divided by 2.0
    
    Note: Calculate saturation
    Let saturation be if delta is equal to 0.0 then 0.0 else (delta divided by (1.0 minus Math.absolute_value of (2.0 times lightness minus 1.0)))
    
    Note: Calculate hue
    Let hue be if delta is equal to 0.0 then 0.0 else calculate_hue with r as r and g as g and b as b and max_val as max_val and delta as delta
    
    Return HSLColor with:
        hue as hue
        saturation as saturation
        lightness as lightness

Process called "calculate_hue" that takes r as Float and g as Float and b as Float and max_val as Float and delta as Float returns Float:
    Let hue be 0.0
    
    If max_val is equal to r:
        Set hue to ((g minus b) divided by delta) modulo 6.0
    Otherwise if max_val is equal to g:
        Set hue to ((b minus r) divided by delta) plus 2.0
    Otherwise:
        Set hue to ((r minus g) divided by delta) plus 4.0
    
    Set hue to hue times 60.0
    If hue is less than 0.0:
        Set hue to hue plus 360.0
    
    Return hue

Process called "rgb_to_oklch" that takes red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer returns OKLCHColor:
    Note: Simplified OKLCH conversion (production would use proper color science)
    Let r be red as Float divided by 255.0
    Let g be green as Float divided by 255.0
    Let b as Float divided by 255.0
    
    Note: Rough approximation of OKLCH conversion
    Let lightness be 0.2126 times r plus 0.7152 times g plus 0.0722 times b
    Let chroma be Math.square_root of ((r minus lightness) times (r minus lightness) plus (g minus lightness) times (g minus lightness) plus (b minus lightness) times (b minus lightness))
    Let hue be Math.arc_tangent_2 with y as (g minus lightness) and x as (r minus lightness) times 180.0 divided by Math.pi
    
    If hue is less than 0.0:
        Set hue to hue plus 360.0
    
    Return OKLCHColor with:
        lightness as lightness
        chroma as chroma
        hue as hue

Process called "rgb_to_hex" that takes red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer returns String:
    Let red_hex be integer_to_hex with value as red
    Let green_hex be integer_to_hex with value as green
    Let blue_hex be integer_to_hex with value as blue
    
    Return "#" Joined with red_hex Joined with green_hex Joined with blue_hex

Process called "integer_to_hex" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Let hex_chars be "0123456789ABCDEF"
    Let high_digit be value divided by 16
    Let low_digit be value modulo 16
    
    Let high_char be hex_chars at index high_digit
    Let low_char be hex_chars at index low_digit
    
    Return high_char Joined with low_char

